docs.abstract: After 24 years in charge of the left-leaning weekly’s editorial operations, the second woman to serve as its editor will give up running that role while continuing on as publisher.
docs.snippet: After 24 years in charge of the left-leaning weekly’s editorial operations, the second woman to serve as its editor will give up running that role while continuing on as publisher.
docs.lead_paragraph: For 24 years, the editor and publisher Katrina vanden Heuvel has been the public face of The Nation, the oldest continuously published weekly in the United States. On June 15, she will give up her job as day-to-day editor, and be succeeded in the role by D. D. Guttenplan, an author long associated with the magazine.

headline.main: Katrina vanden Heuvel to Step Down as Editor of The Nation
headline.print_headline: Nation Editor To Step Down But Stay On As Publisher
